Paper title: {{ title }}
Paper abstract:
<abstract>
{{ abstract }}
</abstract>

Reason through these steps before answering:
1. Is the abstract actually about the claim's subject? If it is not, the stance is off_topic.
2. If it is relevant, do the reported findings affirm the claim (supports), conflict with it
   (contradicts), or neither because they are hedged, inconclusive, or only tangential (neutral)?
3. Choose the single sentence or phrase from the abstract that best justifies your choice.

Then give your judgement:
- stance: exactly one of supports, contradicts, neutral, off_topic.
- snippet: that justifying text copied verbatim from the abstract, with no paraphrase or edits.
- rationale: one sentence explaining how the snippet settles the stance.

When the abstract is too thin to tell, answer neutral rather than guessing.
